   ░ ██          http://www.criterion.com/asp/release.asp?id=98          ██ ░
   ░ ██                                                                  ██ ░
   ░ ██     What's up with this internal crap from AEN  lately,  you     ██ ░
   ░ ██     may ask? Even though it's seven weeks since our internal     ██ ░
   ░ ██     of Sansho it's still not our style, right? Don't  worry,     ██ ░
   ░ ██     we won't make a bad habit out of it. But this particular     ██ ░
   ░ ██     movie... It's something really special about it.             ██ ░
   ░ ██                                                                  ██ ░
   ░ ██     It is this movie, Michelangelo Antonioni's L' Avventura,     ██ ░
   ░ ██     that once long ago brought me in to the world  of  black     ██ ░
   ░ ██     and white cinema. So one could say the two of us  shares     ██ ░
   ░ ██     a special bound. I love this movie with all of my heart;     ██ ░
   ░ ██     I love the directing, acting, the cinematography,  yes -     ██ ░
   ░ ██     everything.                                                  ██ ░
   ░ ██                                                                  ██ ░
   ░ ██     Enjoy, friends!                                              ██ ░
   ░ ██                                                                  ██ ░
   ░ ██     Last but certainly not the least, I would like to dedic-     ██ ░
   ░ ██     ate this release to in my opinion the two  most  notable     ██ ░
   ░ ██     directors of all time. Ingmar Bergman  and  Michelangelo     ██ ░
   ░ ██     Antonioni passed away last monday. The news about Anton-     ██ ░
   ░ ██     ioni struck me right in this minute, I'm almost shocked.     ██ ░
   ░ ██     I had been preparing this rip for a long time, I did not     ██ ░
   ░ ██     reckon it would become a tribute to my favorite director     ██ ░
   ░ ██     ever. I'm sad to witness more and more  great  directors     ██ ░
   ░ ██     passing away as the audience of the 21:th century  seems     ██ ░
   ░ ██     to be more interested in the  newest  blockbusters  than     ██ ░
   ░ ██     the essential historiy of cinema.                            ██ ░
